Advertisement Posted: Wednesday, October 7, 2015 6:16 pm | Updated: 7:26 pm, Wed Oct 7, 2015. Travis volleyball sweeps Hightower, ties for third in 23-6A By Jack Marrion jmarrion@hcnonline.com   Travis volleyball team met its closest challenger for fourth place in the District 23-6A, the position holding the final playoff spot. 
After a 25-22, 25-18, 25-23 sweep of Hightower on Oct. 6, the Lady Tigers are four matches ahead of the rest of the pack with seven remaining. They improved to 8-3 in 23-6A play, tying Clements for third place. 
Kendall King led Travis with eight kills and three blocks, with Destiny Jones contributing seven kills and three blocks. Hannah Callison added six kills. 
Raven Robertson produced 12 digs, also registering five kills. Kendall Wolfe set a match-high 22 assists and Riley Marsh recorded a team-high 14 digs and two aces. 
Travis has a challenging week ahead with undefeated Austin and Clements looming. The Lady Tigers look to even the season series with both. 
Austin improved to 10-0 in district with a 25-14, 25-17, 25-20 victory against Clements. Dylan Brinkman led the way with 13 kills and 14 digs for the Lady Bulldogs. 
Paige Swinney added 10 kills and four aces, Madison Rhoder had nine kills and Maddie Nicholson amassed 21 assists and 10 digs. 
Kempner turned back Elsik to improved to 3-8 and knock the Lady Rams to 4-7, tied with Hightower for fifth place. Hightower gets Elsik next, followed by Hastings. Kempner plays at Hastings and hosts Dulles. 
In District 23-5A, Bush maintained its share of third place despite a fierce rally by Elkins. Monet Jones notched 21 kills and five aces for the Lady Knights, but the Lady Broncos prevailed 25-19, 25-18, 22-25, 22-25, 15-10. 
Bush is 5-3 in district, tied with Ball, which held off Marshall 22-25, 25-18, 26-24, 25-16. 
Ridge Point kept pace with undefeated Santa Fe with a 25-15, 25-9, 25-21 victory against Willowridge. The Lady Panthers are 6-1, one match behind the Santa Fe team they face Oct. 9.
